285 g Jumbo Shrimp
2 unit(s) Flatbread
113 g Baby Tomatoes
56 g Arugula and Spinach Mix
1 unit(s) Lemon
3 unit(s) Radish
½ cup Monterey Jack Cheese, shredded
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
4 tbsp White Cooking Wine
2 unit(s) Chicken Broth Concentrate
4 g Chili Flakes
1 g Garlic Powder
0.13 tsp Sugar*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450˚F.
Wash and dry all produce.
Zest, then juice half the lemon. Cut the remaining lemon into wedges.
Halve tomatoes. Season with salt and pepper.
Thinly slice radishes into half-moons.

Drain and rinse shrimp, then pat dry with paper towels. Season with salt, pepper and half the garlic powder (use all for 4 servings).
In a large non-stick pan, melt 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) butter over medium.
When the pan is hot, add shrimp. Cook for 2-3 min, stirring often, until shrimp just turn pink.**
Add white wine, broth concentrates and 1/8 tsp (1/4 tsp) sugar. Cook for 30 sec, stirring often, until fragrant.
Remove from heat, then stir in 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) lemon zest.
Cover shrimp and sauce to keep warm.

On a foil-lined baking sheet, arrange flatbreads. (NOTE: For 4 servings, use 2 foil-lined baking sheets. Bake in the middle and bottom of the oven.)
Bake flatbreads in the middle of the oven for 3-4 min, until golden. (TIP: Keep an eye on them so they don't burn.)

Remove flatbreads from the oven.
Top with Monterey Jack cheese and half the Parmesan.
Return flatbreads to the oven and bake for 4-5 min, until cheese melts. (TIP: Keep an eye on them so they don't burn.)

Meanwhile, in a large bowl, whisk together 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) sugar, 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) lemon juice and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil. Season with salt and pepper.
Add arugula-spinach mix, tomatoes and radishes. Toss to coat.

Carefully cut flatbreads in halve crosswise, then cut into equal-sized strips.
Divide jumbo shrimp and white wine sauce between bowls. Alongside, divide cheesy bread dippers and salad between plates.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan over salad.
Sprinkle chili flakes over shrimp, if desired.